@candyleer Thanks for reporting this issue. The reason parentApplicationInstanceId is empty, because there is no need. For across thread, applicationInstanceId of parent is same as the current applicationInstanceId. 

Of course, this is a little harm to add this field into CROSS_THREAD REF. Just send one or two more bytes. So I think the easier way is to accept your proposal. Please send the pull request as soon as possible.

We are going to froze codes for preparing the next release.

We can add a new service to check application id and instance id when agent reconnect to collector.
Flow is: 
```
connect -> check
if(found){
   return true then agent send segments to collector.
}else{
   return false then 
   1. agent clean all the registered id cache
   2. re-register application, instance
   3. replace ids in segments or give up
}
```

> for current version ,one request contains 2 exit span and 3 local span
for above image. I think AsyncThread/excute and /test are enough (one local and one exit)

Yes, agree. And be advised, local span should be in main thread, exit span should match the real HTTP request.

@wu-sheng  the work flow of `Async http client` can be drawed as:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11530760/39812286-98832838-53be-11e8-9358-488f5299cc2d.png)

there are 3 thread to work ,so it's hard to start the local span in main thread ,the data is transfer by queue but not `new Thread()` directly, so do you have any proposal for this to trace? I can trace `thread-3` ,but it's hard to trace `main` to `thread-3` especially it's based on queue.

